track.name: I Never Talk to Strangers
comments: I'm in love with this song
Good song from a very good album.  Tom and Bette covering each end of the musical scale vocally.
sincerely wish there were more bette & tom duets.
Well, only suckers fall in love with perfect strangers.

It's so weird hearing Tom Waits & Bette Midler singing together... but I'm not knocking it. It's just two very different musical phases I went through in very different times of my life (like in Grade 6, I went through a Bette Midler/Carpenters/Barry Manilow phase and during high school and now in college I've been in love with Tom Waits, so it tickles my fancy to hear the combination of these two phases I went through.)
There's an odd magic to this track. My brain says no but my soul says yes.
I never learned I haven't talk to strangers. Sorry mumy.
well only suckers fall in love with perfect strangers
